  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nDealers are currently in long gamma regime with SPX at 6557 sitting below the flip at 6574, meaning they're buying this dip and providing stabilizing flow - the massive positive gamma walls from 6565-6585 create a strong magnet effect that should cap volatility and pull price back toward that cluster. The recent GEX surge combined with spot trading below flip suggests dealers just absorbed significant long gamma positions and are now actively hedging by buying futures into weakness, creating natural support at current levels. Watch 6565 as the first major gamma wall for mean reversion target, while a break below 6500 would flip dealers to short gamma and trigger accelerated selling flow.",
